   "mulle-c-string-escape [-h|--help|help]\n"
   "\n"
   "\xe2\x9e\xbf mulle-c-string-escape turns data into C-strings\n"
   "\n"
   "It will escape non-ASCII characters to hex or octal, and use C-escapes f"
   "or the\n"
   "known C escapes. It will separate the output into lines not longer than"
   "\n"
   "80 charactes.\n"
   "\n"
   "You can easily `#include` the output, or just copy/paste it.\n"
   "\n"
   "Reads from standard input and writes to standard output. You can also us"
   "e\n"
   "it on binary files.\n"
   "\n"
   "So use it with redirection like:\n"
   "\n"
   "mulle-c-string-escape < mytext.txt\n"
